29/06/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Economy and Finance Minister Giorgos Alogoskoufis called for serious dialogue Tuesday (28 June) about the country's social security system, stressing that a long-term solution must be found. 
He described ongoing structural reforms as a bitter pill that must be swallowed to strengthen the economy. 
As parliament debates a government bill to reform social security, banking sector employees are staging a fourth week of protests over the proposed restructuring of their pensions. 
(Kathimerini - 29/06/05; ANA, MPA - 28/06/05)
